FBIS4-63545 "drsov099_f_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-099 Daily Report 21 May 1994 National Affairs To Request Powers in Crimean Constitution Crisis To Request Powers in Crimean Constitution Crisis LD2105165994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1600 GMT 21 May 94 LD2105165994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] Leonid Kravchuk, president of Ukraine, intends to ask the parliament for the relevant powers if the supreme soviet of Crimea does not revoke the decision to restore the 1992 constitution, Nykola Mykhalchenko, head of the presidential service on questions of internal policy reported. He did not reply to the question as to whether these powers meant the introduction of direct presidential rule or of a state of emergency in Crimea.
